# Lambda Python Conventions

## Structure
- Handler: `lambda_handler(event, context)` in `app.py`
- Constants at module top, UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- Private helpers prefixed with `_`
- Classes for stateful API clients (e.g., `LinkedInPoster`)

## Error Handling
- Catch `botocore.exceptions.ClientError` for AWS calls
- Use `requests.raise_for_status()` instead of manual status checks
- Use `logger.exception()` to include stack traces
- Return structured `{"statusCode": N, "body": json.dumps({...})}` from handler

## Logging
- Use `logger.info("message: %s", var)` (lazy formatting, not f-strings)
- Log at appropriate levels: `info` for flow, `warning` for recoverable, `error`/`exception` for failures

## HTTP
- All `requests.get/post/put` calls must include `timeout`
- Extract shared headers (e.g., User-Agent) into module-level constants
